<h2 class="nounderline"><a name="maincontent">Coordinator of the Minnesota Parent Center (MPC)</a></h2>

<p>
<strong>POSITION</strong>: Coordinator of the Minnesota Parent Center (MPC)<br />
<strong>SUPERVISOR</strong>: Paula Goldberg, PACER Executive Director<br />
<strong>STATUS</strong>: Full-time, Exempt
</p>

<h3>Responsibilities:</h3>
<ul>
	<li>Implement and manage the goals and activities of grant designed to increase parent involvement in education and assist local schools to design and implement parental involvement policies.</li>
	<li>Collaborate with a broad cross-section of people including families that are economically and educationally disadvantaged, parents of young children, school personnel from across the state, collaborative partners, and internal staff.</li>
	<li>Supervise MPC staff to accomplish short and long term goals of the center.</li>
	<li>Provide collaborative training and technical assistance to school personnel and families on method to improve student achievement and strengthen parent-school partnerships.</li>
	<li>Act as managing editor and author of all MPC materials; including, handouts, brochures, manuals, booklets, and curriculums.</li>
	<li>Present workshops, educational activities and trainings in communities throughout the state.</li>
	<li>Coordinate a thorough evaluation of all activities and outcomes.</li>
	<li>Participate in managing the budget.</li>
	<li>Develop and carry out activities to reach underserved and under represented families.</li>
	<li>Other activities as required.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Desired Qualifications:</h3>
<ul>
	<li>College degree in relevant area </li>
	<li>Experience in managing </li>
	<li>Knowledge of the public education system</li>
	<li>Experience in the early childhood education</li>
	<li>Experience in working with economically and educationally disadvantaged families</li>
	<li>Proven self-starter with ability to work with others.</li>
	<li>Proven leadership and supervisory skills</li>
	<li>Ability to provide transportation and flexibility to travel</li>
	<li>Excellent organization skills, accuracy and attention to detail </li>
	<li>Strong verbal and written communication skills </li>
	<li>Ability to use time efficiently and oversee multiple tasks and goals </li>
</ul>

<p>
Parents of children with disabilities and persons of color are strongly encouraged to apply.<br />
Salary will be based on experience and qualifications.<br />
Position is open until filled.
</p>

